{
  "texts": [
    "Then, the camera's position and orientation are determined relative to the desired object (target) and the pose is estimated from 2D images using pixel correspondence and 3D object points [59].",
    "The intrinsic parameters of the camera contribute to pixel-by-pixel point cloud projection from the depth images to 3D points.",
    "In the next step, the camera is calibrated to correct possible errors, while in real-time applications it is calibrated to obtain the desired coordinate system.",
    "Thereupon the features are extracted, and homologous points are detected between previous and current frames at each given time and matched.",
    "Then, a low-resolution sparse point cloud is generated."
  ]
}